    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER - REASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>REMOTE CONTROL (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302365">Figure 65</hotlnk>)
            </title>
            <figure id="f1302365" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302365" filename="../figg13/G1302365.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Check Remote Control Dimension</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After packing the remote control housing cavity with grease, install the rod.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set the shift finger in place and secure it with a set screw. Tighten to 40 to 50
                    ft-lbs. (54 to 68 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the boot over the rod onto the remote control housing. Secure it with two tie-down
                    straps.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Put the outer shift lever onto the splined end of the shift rod. Install the set screw
                    and tighten it to 40 to 50 ft-lbs. (54 to 68 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reassemble the selection lever subassembly and bolt it into place.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Screw the jam nuts, turnbuckle and ball joints onto the tie rod. Grease the ball
                    joints.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a spacer on the ball joint studs. Attach it to the selection lever subassembly and
                    remote control housing. Place the interlock in the rear position and install the interlock.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the remote control gasket and assembly onto the transmission. Tighten the bolts
                    to 31 to 45 ft-lbs. (42 to 61 N&#8226;m). Then adjust the linkage according to the specifications in
                    CTS-5094, Shift Control Linkage, in GROUP 13 - TRANSMISSION of the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the remote control dimensions shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302365">Figure 65</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
